In the context of many-electron atoms and the central field approximation: If the fine-structure splitting between levels is $Delta E$, how is the spin-orbit coupling constant $lambda$ estimated using the Landé interval rule?
#pagebreak()
#set page(width: a_width, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
$lambda = Delta E / J$
#pagebreak()
#set page(width: a_width, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
$lambda = Delta E / Z$
#pagebreak()
#set page(width: a_width, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
$lambda = Delta E / (L dot S)$
#pagebreak()
#set page(width: a_width, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
$lambda = Delta E / n$
